<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-08-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="140" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Hicks</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <hi rend="italic"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-08-20">August 20,
                                        1906</date></hi>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>President Roosevelt has cabled directly to President of Chile an
                            expression of intense sympathy felt at the appalling disaster that has
                            befallen her. You will supplement this by the proper representations at
                            the foreign office.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>